Ed, SW &amp; Cook,<br><br>
I have had some back-channel communication with ClassLass, and know her name and e-mail address.  In her discussions with me, she has come across as authenic.  <br><br>
When we were in-country, we had an authenication code.  I remember one pickup when the Jolly's were inbound on a survivor, and asked him to authenicate.  He tried, but couldn't remember the codes.  They were just about to turn off when the damnest streak of blue language came in over the headset that you've ever heard, something which no non-native speaker could keep up with.  The pilots decided that this was a good enough demonstration, and made the pickup.<br><br>
How about giving ClassLass a bit of a break, and listening to what she wants to say now.  I think she's on the level, and she has given me some helpful suggestions. 
